-- Sequence utilities: notations for common sequence patterns.

-- adjacent seq
-- Produces the set of consecutive pairs from a sequence.
-- {(seq[0], seq[1]), (seq[1], seq[2]), ...}
-- Usage: ∀ (prev, next) ∈ adjacent scores: prev > next
notation adjacent seq = {(seq[i], seq[i+1]) | i ∈ {0..#seq-2}}
